properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 7 at 6:16PM CST until January 8 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...A PERIOD OF LAKE EFFECT SNOW WILL DEVELOP THIS EVENING AND
CONTINUE INTO WEDNESDAY MORNING...

.Colder air will continue to filter into the region in the wake
of a cold front into tonight. This cold air will help support some
lake effect snow showers over the higher terrain of Iron County
in northwest Wisconsin, beginning this evening and persisting into
Wednesday morning. This snow could impact the Wednesday morning
commute for the Kimball, Montreal, Gile, and Hurley areas. This
cold air and breezy winds will also lead to very cold wind chills
tonight across most of northeastern Minnesota with readings of -25
to -35 degrees expected.

More snow will develop Wednesday night into Thursday. The highest
accumulation is expected along portions of the North Shore which
may see 6 inches or more.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills as low as 30 below zero expected.

* WHERE...Portions of east central, north central and northeast
Minnesota.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM CST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM CST WEDNESDAY
